==Arabic==
===Etymology===
From the verb {{ARchar|[[دق]]}} (dáqqa), to be thin, to be fine, to be small.

===Adjective===
'''{{ARchar|دقيق}}''' (daqīq), {{ARchar|[[دقاق]]}} (daqāq), {{ARchar|[[ادقة]]}} (adíqqa)

# [[fine]], [[thin]]
# [[delicate]], [[fragile]], [[frail]]
# [[little]], [[small]], [[tiny]], [[minute]]
# [[subtle]], [[puny]]
# [[paltry]], [[petty]], [[trivial]], [[trifling]]
# [[precise]], [[accurate]], [[exact]]

===Noun===
'''{{ARchar|دقيق}}''' (daqīq) {{m}} ''uncountable''

# [[flour]], [[meal]]

